					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Wla is a terrible assembler. It's full of bugs and unintuitive features. But, it's fully adequate for SPC-700 programming, since you just need to write your music engine, and you've got a flat 64K memory space. But the fact that you have to program a second processor just to get sound is a lot more complex than using the NES APU. It's kind of like the old BASIC home computers versus having to deal with a whole OS just to output PCM.</div>

